        "description": {
            "value": "<p><strong>Access</strong> You're from Isger or a member of the Sisterhood of the Golden Erinys.</p><hr /><p>The fighting style of the Sisterhood of the Golden Erinys is rooted in their understanding of devils. You gain the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.Item.Additional Lore] general feat for Devil Lore. When you choose this feat, you can choose to become sanctified as unholy.</p>\n<p>You gain access to the asp coil. You have familiarity with the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.Asp Coil] and @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.Scourge], treating them as simple weapons for the purposes of proficiency. If you're unholy, your Strikes using those weapons and your unarmed Strikes gain the unholy trait.</p><hr /><p>Special If you have the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.Item.Monastic Weaponry] feat, the asp coil gains the monk trait for you.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.journals.JournalEntry.vx5FGEG34AxI2dow.JournalEntryPage.UO4n5TKJSA1o4Cup]{Sister of the Golden Erinys}</p>"
        },
